President Cyril Ramaphosa has wished strength to those who have lost someone they love to the disease. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has offered his condolences to victims of COVID-19. That's as South Africa passed the one thousand mark of coronavirus deaths. READ: COVID-19: SA death toll at 1080 Ramaphosa has wished strength to those who have lost someone they love to the disease. He's praised South Africans who have acted accordingly in reducing the spread of COVID-19. READ: SA Lockdown: Ramaphosa announces COVID-19 'hot spots' The president says government has used lockdown time to prepare the health system as much as possible. Thousands of hospital and quarantine beds have been secured as a result. Ramaphosa warns higher lockdown alert levels will be imposed for specific parts of the country should it be necessary. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.